{"body_text": "The opt-out study action will need to check certain preferences to determine if it should install the study add-on or not. We'll need to add an API to the driver for reading preferences.\nI think mirroring Preferences.jsm on the driver is our best bet:\nnormandy.preferences.get('foo.bar.baz', 'default_value');\nnormandy.preferences.has('foo.bar.baz')\nnormandy.preferences.isSet('foo.bar.baz');\n@crankycoder How does the API above look to you?", "labels": [], "number": 746, "assignee": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Osmose/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Osmose/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Osmose/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/Osmose", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Osmose/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/Osmose", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Osmose/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://avatars1.githubusercontent.com/u/193106?v=4", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Osmose/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Osmose/received_events", "gravatar_id": "", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Osmose/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "site_admin": false, "login": "Osmose", "type": "User", "id": 193106, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Osmose/followers"}, "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/mozilla/normandy", "closed_at": "2017-08-03T20:56:10Z", "body_html": "<p>The opt-out study action will need to check certain preferences to determine if it should install the study add-on or not. We'll need to add an API to the driver for reading preferences.</p>\n<p>I think mirroring <a href=\"https://dxr.mozilla.org/mozilla-central/source/toolkit/modules/Preferences.jsm\" rel=\"nofollow\">Preferences.jsm</a> on the driver is our best bet:</p>\n<div class=\"highlight highlight-source-js\"><pre><span class=\"pl-smi\">normandy</span>.<span class=\"pl-smi\">preferences</span>.<span class=\"pl-c1\">get</span>(<span class=\"pl-s\"><span class=\"pl-pds\">'</span>foo.bar.baz<span class=\"pl-pds\">'</span></span>, <span class=\"pl-s\"><span class=\"pl-pds\">'</span>default_value<span class=\"pl-pds\">'</span></span>);\n<span class=\"pl-smi\">normandy</span>.<span class=\"pl-smi\">preferences</span>.<span class=\"pl-c1\">has</span>(<span class=\"pl-s\"><span class=\"pl-pds\">'</span>foo.bar.baz<span class=\"pl-pds\">'</span></span>)\n<span class=\"pl-smi\">normandy</span>.<span class=\"pl-smi\">preferences</span>.<span class=\"pl-en\">isSet</span>(<span class=\"pl-s\"><span class=\"pl-pds\">'</span>foo.bar.baz<span class=\"pl-pds\">'</span></span>);</pre></div>\n<p><a class=\"user-mention\" href=\"https://github.com/crankycoder\">@crankycoder</a> How does the API above look to you?</p>", "id": 227526979, "title": "Add driver functions for reading preferences", "comments": 2, "state": "closed", "body": "The opt-out study action will need to check certain preferences to determine if it should install the study add-on or not. We'll need to add an API to the driver for reading preferences.\r\n\r\nI think mirroring [Preferences.jsm](https://dxr.mozilla.org/mozilla-central/source/toolkit/modules/Preferences.jsm) on the driver is our best bet:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nnormandy.preferences.get('foo.bar.baz', 'default_value');\r\nnormandy.preferences.has('foo.bar.baz')\r\nnormandy.preferences.isSet('foo.bar.baz');\r\n```\r\n\r\n@crankycoder How does the API above look to you?", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/mozilla/normandy/issues/746/events", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/mozilla/normandy/issues/746/labels{/name}", "author_association": "MEMBER", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/mozilla/normandy/issues/746/comments", "html_url": "https://github.com/mozilla/normandy/issues/746", "updated_at": "2018-01-30T17:39:19Z", "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Osmose/following{/other_user}", "e